author: CNN
description: “Sports and politics have always gone together,” says CNN Contributor and host of “The Cari Champion Show” on Prime Video, Cari Champion. Thursday Night Football’s moment of silence for Charlie Kirk was just the latest example of how sports and politics have been intertwined for a long time. #cnn #sports #politics #shorts
title: Kirk moment of silence shows politics have always been present in sports

author: CNN
description:
The suspect in the murder of Charlie Kirk, Tyler Robinson, is being held at a county jail in Spanish Fork, Utah, on multiple initial charges, an officer of the Utah County Jail told CNN this morning.

The charges that allow Robinson to be held include aggravated murder, felony discharge of a firearm and obstruction of justice, the officer said. #CNN #News
title: Suspect in Kirk killing charged with aggravated murder

author: CNN
description: Liat Beinin Atzili, who was held hostage by Hamas, and director Brandon Kramer spoke with CNN's Christiane Amanpour about documenting her family’s lives while she was in captivity for a new documentary "Holding Liat." #cnn  #News
title: ‘Holding Liat’: A look at how one hostage family navigated a nightmare

author: CNN
description: An Immigration and Customs Enforcement officer fatally shot a man in a Chicago suburb after he allegedly resisted arrest and dragged an officer during a vehicle stop, according to the Department of Homeland Security. CNN's Shimon Prokupecz reports.
title: ICE kills man who allegedly dragged officer during arrest

author: CNN
description: They may rain on your parade, or photobomb your sunset pictures, but clouds are more interesting than you might think. Here are some unexpected facts about these familiar sights. #CNN #News
title: 5 things you didn't know about clouds

author: CNN
description: CNN's Elizabeth Wagmeister speaks with first-time Emmys host Nate Bargatze. He plans to donate $100k to The Boys and Girls Club of America at the event, but there's a catch. He's going to need Hollywood's help to pull it off. #CNN #News
title: Emmy’s host Nate Bargatze says he won’t be mean to celebs. But Colbert jokes aren’t off limits

author: CNN
description: French authorities now believe that a series of mysterious incidents in Paris may be the work of foreign agents, possibly working on behalf of Russia, aiming to stoke tensions. CNN's Melissa Bell reports. #pigs #heads #mosque #parisfrance
title: Are foreign agents stoking tensions in France?

author: CNN
description:
ICE target is shot and killed after injuring officer in Chicago-area traffic stop, DHS says
A target of an Immigration and Customs Enforcement traffic stop dragged an ICE officer with a vehicle while resisting arrest in a Chicago suburb Friday morning, prompting the officer to fatally shoot the suspect and leaving the officer with severe injuries, the Department of Homeland Security said. The slain target of the stop, Silverio Villegas-Gonzalez, was an undocumented immigrant with a history of reckless driving, according to DHS. CNN’s Shimon Prokupecz reports.   #CNN #News
title: ICE target is shot and killed after injuring officer in Chicago-area traffic stop, DHS says

author: CNN
description: Kentucky nurse Misty Combs revived an unresponsive baby raccoon using CPR after discovering the raccoon and its sibling stuck in a dumpster, having feasted on fermented peaches from a local distillery. After a trip to the vet, the raccoon was released back into the wild. #cnn #news
title: Nurse gives lifesaving CPR to drunk raccoon

author: CNN
description:
NATO has launched an initiative to reinforce the defense of Europe’s eastern flank after a Russian drone incursion into Polish airspace this week, NATO Secretary-General Mark Rutte announced on Friday. 

The “Eastern Sentry” operation will commence in the coming days and will involve assets from Denmark, France, the United Kingdom, Germany, and others, Rutte said.  #CNN #News
title: NATO launches ‘Eastern Sentry’ operation in response to Russian drone incursions

author: CNN
description: Satellite imagery shows more than 1,800 buildings in and around Gaza City have been destroyed or damaged since Israel announced plans to take over the city, CNN analysis finds. The demolitions — largely of homes and tent camps — have forced displaced Palestinians to flee again, with little space left for makeshift shelters as a full Israeli invasion looms, reports CNN’s Jeremy Diamond. #cnn #news
title: Satellite imagery shows destruction in Gaza City

author: CNN
description:
Tyler Robinson, the suspect in the fatal shooting of Charlie Kirk, was taken into custody at 10 p.m. local time Thursday in Utah, FBI Director Kash Patel announced. 

“In less than 36 hours – 33 to be precise – thanks to the full weight of the federal government and leading out with the partners here in the state of Utah and Gov. Cox, the suspect was apprehended in historic time period,” said Patel.  #CNN #News
title: Suspect in custody for Kirk killing is 22-year-old from Utah

title: Suspect in Kirk killing in custody, Trump says

author: CNN
description:
Dr. Sanjay Gupta sits down at 92nd Street Y in New York with his friend and ultra-marathoner @richroll to talk about how our brain can create pain proactively and protectively. They also discuss how a good memory might have something to do with your chronic pain – and how to move through, with, and past those painful reminders.

Listen to the full episode of CNN's Chasing Life podcast: http://swap.fm/l/clyt0915

#cnn #news #health #pain #sanjaygupta #drsanjaygupta #richroll
title: What pain taught ultra-marathoner Rich Roll | Chasing Life

author: CNN
description: Brazil's former President Jair Bolsonaro was sentenced to 27 years and three months in prison by the Brazilian Supreme Court who found him guilty of attempting to overturn Brazil's 2022 election, including plotting a coup d’état on January 8, 2023. Prosecutors alleged part of the plot included plans to assassinate the president-elect. Bolsonaro and other defendants in the trial have denied any wrongdoing. #CNN #news
title: Trump reacts to Bolsonaro conviction

author: CNN
description:
CNN's Erin Burnett speaks to Henry Dells, who had asked Charlie Kirk a question before Kirk was shot.
The people who were in line at Charlie Kirk’s event were selected about five minutes ahead of time, and they all discussed together as a group what they were going to ask, according to Dells.
About four to five people were selected to ask Kirk questions and were going to have topics ranging from abortion to race, he said. #CNN #News
title: Man who asked Kirk a question before he was shot speaks out

author: CNN
description: The suspected shooter who critically wounded two students at Evergreen High School in Colorado during their third week of classes this semester appeared to have been “radicalized by some extreme network,” officials said Thursday. #CNN #News
title: Denver-area high school shooting suspect was ‘radicalized,’ officials say
